{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fake Claim Campaign: End The Harassment Of People With Invisible Disabilities",
        "additional_details": "- Make \"Fake Claiming\" a specific criminal offence\r\n \r\n- \u201cInclude the letter \"A\" for accessibility in the symbol for accessible facilities in all Government buildings, alongside the wheelchair symbol\"\r\n \r\nDespite the majority of Disabled people having disabilities that cannot be seen (\"invisible disabilities\") there are still widespread misconceptions about disability.\r\n \r\nBecause of this, Disabled people face harassment in public places by people who \"Fake Claim\" them, and do not acknowledge their disability.\r\n \r\nFake Claiming prevents access to services such as accessible parking spaces, accessible toilets, seats on public transport and other assistance, and can lead to threats and abuse when accessing them.",
        "background": "The Government should:\r\n \r\n- Conduct a review of harassment faced by people with invisible disabilities\r\n",
